AMTRAK uses &quot;dual mode&quot; (diesel / third rail electric) Genesis locos
between Albany and NYC (Penn Station).  These locos have third rail
shoes and once they get to the tunnel, they are *supposed* to shut down
the diesel prime mover and run off third rail.

Metro-North has either old (much rebuilt) FL9s (which are 1st generation
&quot;dual mode&quot; locos, also diesel / third rail electric) or &quot;dual mode&quot;
Genesis locos (like AMTRAK uses now).  Again, they are *supposed* to
shut down the diesel prime mover while in the tunnels.

